This paper is about response generation for open domain conversation in chatbots, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new model for response generation that uses dynamic vocabularies, which is a novel approach in NLP. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to train and evaluate the model, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed model, which could place it in the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
